claim.claim-text:
1. A method of forming a multi-gate semiconductor device, comprising:
forming a first fin on a first portion of a semiconductor substrate having a first dopant type;
performing dopant implantation of the first dopant type in a first channel region of the first fin;
performing dopant implantation of a second dopant type in a second channel region of the first fin;
forming a gate electrode layer of the second dopant type over the first channel region of the first fin; and
forming a gate electrode layer of the first dopant type over the second channel region of the first fin.

2. The method of claim 1, further comprising:
forming a second fin on a second portion of a semiconductor substrate having a second dopant type;
performing dopant implantation of the second dopant type in a first channel region of the second fin;
performing dopant implantation of the first dopant type in a second channel region of the second fin;
forming a gate electrode layer of the first dopant type over the first channel region of the second fin; and
forming a gate electrode layer of the second dopant type over the second channel region of the second fin.

7. The method of claim 5, further comprising:
patterning a photoresist over the p-type channel region having the lower VT;
then depositing the p-type gate electrode layer over the n-type channel region having the higher VT;
then removing the photoresist from over the p-type channel region; and
then depositing the n-type gate electrode layer over the p-type channel region.

10. A method of forming a multi-gate semiconductor device, comprising:
forming a first fin;
performing dopant implantation of the first dopant type in a first channel region of the first fin;
performing dopant implantation of a second dopant type in a second channel region of the first fin;
forming a dielectric material layer over at least a portion of the first and second channel regions of the fin;
forming a gate electrode layer of the second dopant type over the first channel region of the first fin; and
forming a gate electrode layer of the first dopant type over the second channel region of the first fin;
wherein the device has a first voltage threshold (VT) at the first channel region and a second VT higher than the first VT at the second channel region.

20. A method of forming a multi-gate semiconductor device, comprising:
forming a first fin on a first portion of a semiconductor substrate having a first dopant type;
forming a second fin on a second portion of the semiconductor substrate having a second dopant type;
performing dopant implantation first dopant type in a respective first channel region of the first and second fins;
performing dopant implantation of a second dopant type in a respective second channel region of the first and second fins;
forming a dielectric material layer over at least a portion of the respective first and second channel regions of the first and second fins;
forming a gate electrode layer of the second dopant type over the respective first channel regions of the first and second fins;
forming a gate electrode layer of the first dopant type over the respective second channel regions of the first and second fins;
wherein the device has a respective first voltage threshold (VT) at the respective first channel regions of the first and second fins;
wherein the device has a respective second VT at the respective second channel regions of the first and second fins, and wherein the respective first VT is higher than the respective second VT;
and wherein the respective difference between work functions at the respective first and second channel regions of the first and second fins is approximately 200 millielectron volts or less.
